\section{Margin}{

\code{margin} is a non-negative clinically meaningful difference threshold.
A pair only declares a winner when the directional gap strictly exceeds
\code{margin}; otherwise the pair ties at this endpoint and falls through to
the next one. \code{nb_binary()} does not expose \code{margin} because binary
values admit only two outcomes.
}

\section{Censoring}{

\code{nb_tte()} accepts a \code{censor_rule} argument. The default
\code{"informative"} matches the conventional Pocock/Buyse rule: if one
subject is censored and the other observed, a winner can only be
declared in the direction the censoring is uninformative about (i.e.,
the censored time is already past the event time). \code{"ignore"} drops
pairs where either subject is censored and treats them as ties at this
level.
